- Do not catch errors; let them propagate to the CLI entry point.

- `VALIDATION_HEADER` must be declared at module scope with `export const`; do not construct it at runtime or vary it per invocation.
- Do not write to stdout, stderr, or call `process.exit()` — return the string and let the caller decide.
- Do not catch errors; let them propagate to the CLI entry point.

- Prefix the entry file with the `#!/usr/bin/env node` shebang line.
- Call `run(filePaths, command)` with the output of parseArgv applied to `process.argv.slice(2)`.
- Use `is(error, ErrorCode)` checks inside catch blocks to branch on specific HINT error conditions before falling back to printing `String(error)`.
- Do not place `process.exit()` calls outside of run; all lifecycle decisions belong there.

